The photocatalytic property of the coatings was studied by methylene blue (C16H18N3SCl) degradation (5 mg/l) in the presence of sunlight (using methane halide lamp) and UV radiation (using UV-c Philips, 1.5 W lamp). The test duration was 30, 60, 90, 120, 150, and 180 min after which the relevant concentrations were calculated by a spectrophotometer. By drawing the C/C0 curves as a function of time, the amounts of removed colors caused by the photocatalytic activity of the coatings could be comparable [29]:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
